<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-16T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-16T15:00:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 L 76/3: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-16T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 16,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>148. Your 262 June 15, 8 P.M.</p>
                        <p>Department approves suggested procedure merely to acknowledge receipt of
                            note and attend Li’s reception, thus dealing with the situation as a new
                            administration and not a new government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>